						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in a field near a well by the side of the cart-track leading to Kōḍiguḍḷapāḍu.</p>						

						<p>This undated record may be assigned to the 9th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. It seems to record a gift of the Śiddhāya tax. The details about the donor and the donee are lost. It mentions Rācha-Preggaḍa Daṇḍiya Kommaṇa-Raṭṭoḍi and a few others as witnesses.</p>						

						</summary>
